EWN has received reports of dense smoke across the South Peninsula. CAPE TOWN - Firefighters are struggling to access a large vegetation fire on the mountain slopes above Newlands Forest. EWN has received reports of dense smoke across the South Peninsula. Fire and rescue services' Theo Layne said: “We have 20 firefighters on the scene assisted by Table Mountain rangers, most of the fire is inaccessible and we will be on scene for some time.”